---
---

<section id="stakes" class="py-[var(--spacing-section)] border-t border-slate-gray">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8 lg:gap-16">
      <!-- Left: dramatic question -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-7" data-animate="headline">
        <h2 class="font-heading text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-4xl); line-height: 1.05; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          Your space is telling a story right now.
          <span class="block text-smoke-gray mt-2">Is it the right one?</span>
        </h2>
      </div>

      <!-- Right: three pointed statements -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-5 lg:pt-4 flex flex-col justify-center gap-8" data-animate="fade" data-animate-delay="1">
        <div class="pl-6 border-l-2 border-slate-gray">
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            Blank walls signal vacancy. Every day your building says nothing, it says something about your business.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-6 border-l-2 border-slate-gray">
          <p class="font-body text-shadow-gray" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            Generic murals feel like they were ordered from a catalog. Technically skilled and completely interchangeable.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pl-6 border-l-2 border-titanium-white">
          <p class="font-body text-titanium-white" style="font-size: var(--text-fluid-base); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);">
            Your space has a story worth telling. If you do not tell it, someone else will decide what your building means.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
